{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "apex", "namespace": "apex", "internal": "rig::SplineInterpolateTransformsArray", "tags": "apex", "since": "20.0", "version": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["rig::SplineInterpolateTransformsArray"], "extent": [119, 161]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generates and samples a spline."], "extent": [161, 201]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generates a spline from a number of input control matrices. The position of the control matrices defines\nthe shape of the generated spline, while the upper 3\u00d73 transform of the control matrices defines the framing\nof the spline. The generated spline is then resampled a ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["numsamples"]}, " times to produce\noutput transforms which are made available on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["resampled"]}, " port. Additional twists can be applied to the\noutput transforms via the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["twists"]}, " port."], "extent": [201, 657]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The output transforms are interpolated based on the sample\u2019s neighboring input transforms, and then adjusted such that\nthe ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["tangent"]}, " vector points towards the next sample. The default tangent vector is the -Z axis, which implies that,\nby default, the control matrices should also have their -Z axis pointing in the spline\u2019s desired tangent direction.\nIf the control matrices use a different local tangent vector to define their tangent direction, the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["tangent"]}, " port\nshould be updated accordingly. For example, if the control matrices use the +X axis as the tangent direction, then\n", {"type": "ui", "text": ["tangent"]}, " should be updated as ", {"type": "code", "text": ["(1, 0, 0)"]}, "."], "extent": [657, 1289]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Internally, the spline generated from the control matrices is a bezier curve of order ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["order"]}, ". This means that the\nnumber of control matrices must satisfy the equation ", {"type": "code", "text": ["number of cvs % (order-1)"]}, ". While this constraint may be lifted\nin a future version of houdini, users can work around this by generating a nurbs curve with the desired number of\ncontrol points (with a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["transform"]}, " point attribute) and use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms.html"}, " to sample the\ncontrol curve."], "extent": [1289, 1768]}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1768, 1776], "body": [{"type": "inputs_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["cvs"], "role": "item", "extent": [1776, 1785], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The control matrices used to generate, and frame, a control spline. The number of control matrices must satisfy the\n    equation ", {"type": "code", "text": ["number of cvs % (order-1)"]}, "."], "extent": [1810, 1973]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Matrix4Array"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["twists"], "role": "item", "extent": [1973, 1984], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Additional twists (in radians) to add to the output transforms. There does NOT have to be a twist value per cv.\n    Adding a value of 0 and 2*M_PI will twist the output transforms a full rotation about transforms' Z axes.\n    Additional twists values are interpolated linearly between values across the length of the spline."], "extent": [2007, 2337]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "FloatArray"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["numsamples"], "role": "item", "extent": [2337, 2352], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of samples to take for the output spline."], "extent": [2368, 2426]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["order"], "role": "item", "extent": [2426, 2436], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The order of the generated spline curve."], "extent": [2452, 2498]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["smooth"], "role": "item", "extent": [2498, 2508], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When true, adds smooth-step smoothing to the output transforms. The default value is false."], "extent": [2525, 2622]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Bool"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["byedge"], "role": "item", "extent": [2622, 2633], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sample each segment of the spline separately. This samples ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["numsamples"]}, " points on each edge of the input\n    geometry."], "extent": [2650, 2776]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Bool"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2776, 2785], "body": [{"type": "outputs_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "outputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["resampled"], "role": "item", "extent": [2785, 2800], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The resampled transforms."], "extent": [2825, 2856]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Matrix4Array"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Outputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2856, 2865], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSpline", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSpline.html"}], "extent": [2865, 2898]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSplineFromArray", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--ControlSplineFromArray.html"}], "extent": [2898, 2940]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransforms.html"}], "extent": [2940, 2982]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransformsToArray", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SampleSplineTransformsToArray.html"}], "extent": [2982, 3031]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--SplineInterpolateTransforms", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--SplineInterpolateTransforms.html"}], "extent": [3031, 3078]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["rig::SplineInterpolateTransformsArray"], "summary": ["Generates and samples a spline."]}